column5: Started with a slice , then a light yonder, then a glimmer, then a beacon. I followed, as a lost ship at sea, in gale rollers .            Will be calmer waters on the river come next day I am sure. Looking forward to some fishing time with my oldest.
great shots of the sun rise good luck tomorrow
Thanks buddy. They had a stellar day today,. Hope it holds for Sunday.
Looks a bit rolly out there for a toon?
Those were friendly's Paul. Been out on 3-4 ft ones. Rollers are cool, crashing waves, not so much.
LOL, fish in the net makes them easier to tolerate?
I have more confidence in this toon, then I would in my old tinnie in those rollers. I,m a bobber out there. Just call me bobbing for fish guy. LOL
